1
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:10,433
<i>- Hon...
- Are you guys fighting?</i>

2
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:13,200
<i>Some people seem to know exactly
how to push your buttons.</i>

3
00:00:13,333 --> 00:00:14,367
<i> That's why I'm in a bad mood.</i>

4
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:16,533
<i>Didn't I tell you
to stick all night</i>

5
00:00:16,667 --> 00:00:17,800
<i>with your grandmother
and grandfather?</i>

6
00:00:17,933 --> 00:00:19,267
<i> Hey, don't pressure our kid.</i>

7
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:22,133
<i>I'm just thinking about
the future of our child!</i>

8
00:00:22,267 --> 00:00:24,733
<i> Ashley's crazy talented.</i>

9
00:00:24,867 --> 00:00:27,400
<i>Guess she takes
after someone amazing.</i>

10
00:00:27,533 --> 00:00:28,900
<i> She takes after her dad.</i>

11
00:00:30,067 --> 00:00:31,067
<i> Mr. Vergara.</i>

12
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:32,400
<i>Of course I remember you, Thea.</i>

13
00:00:32,533 --> 00:00:34,767
<i>But I haven't been Edward's
partner in almost two years.</i>

14
00:00:34,933 --> 00:00:36,533
<i> Mr. Vergara left me hanging.</i>

15
00:00:36,667 --> 00:00:38,300
<i> And now I'm drowning in debt.</i>

16
00:00:38,433 --> 00:00:40,200
<i> What good is your sorry?</i>

17
00:00:40,333 --> 00:00:41,433
<i> I'll fix this.</i>

18
00:00:41,567 --> 00:00:42,500
<i> I'll fix it.</i>

19
00:00:42,633 --> 00:00:44,367
<i> I don't trust you anymore!</i>

20
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:45,533
<i> This can't be fixed.</i>

21
00:00:45,667 --> 00:00:47,700
<i> I'll handle it myself!</i>

22
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:53,033
<i>You took a lot of guts
to bring this to me.</i>

23
00:00:54,767 --> 00:00:55,733
It's not easy...

24
00:00:57,233 --> 00:01:01,100
standing in front of me
with this kind of mess.

25
00:01:01,233 --> 00:01:06,000
Overdue loans, three suppliers
threatening legal action,

26
00:01:06,133 --> 00:01:07,467
and...

27
00:01:08,633 --> 00:01:11,500
bankruptcy evaluation.

28
00:01:15,133 --> 00:01:16,400
I'm sorry, Dad.

29
00:01:17,333 --> 00:01:19,100
I tried everything
to save the company.

30
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:22,133
But you still failed.

31
00:01:27,533 --> 00:01:29,767
You had one job.

32
00:01:29,900 --> 00:01:31,900
To protect your family name.

33
00:01:35,433 --> 00:01:36,667
And this...

34
00:01:38,700 --> 00:01:40,700
<i> This is what you bring me?</i>

35
00:01:42,667 --> 00:01:46,367
Go ahead! Explain it to me.

36
00:01:48,367 --> 00:01:50,067
- Greg! Greg!
- Dad!

37
00:01:54,667 --> 00:01:57,367
You embarrassed me again!

38
00:01:57,500 --> 00:01:59,900
That tiny bit of trust I had
left?

39
00:02:00,033 --> 00:02:01,267
You threw it away!

40
00:02:02,133 --> 00:02:07,333
Sometimes, I wonder,
are you even my son?

41
00:02:08,467 --> 00:02:11,833
I don't understand
how you ended up my child!

42
00:02:11,967 --> 00:02:13,600
Greg, stop it!

43
00:03:06,733 --> 00:03:07,833
That's enough!

44
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:11,767
Yes, Edward made mistakes.

45
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:16,633
But don't treat him
like he's not even human.

46
00:03:18,533 --> 00:03:20,933
Not everything
about Edward is faulty.

47
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:23,600
He's not the only one to blame.

48
00:03:23,733 --> 00:03:26,167
His mistake was taking
on a business

49
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:28,300
he couldn't handle.

50
00:03:28,433 --> 00:03:31,833
He wasn't ready, he didn't know
what he was doing.

51
00:03:31,967 --> 00:03:34,533
And you! You enabled him again!

52
00:03:34,667 --> 00:03:37,133
Then why did you leave him
to deal with it alone?

53
00:03:37,267 --> 00:03:38,867
I gave him money!

54
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:43,467
You know that's not
all he needed, Greg!

55
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:45,467
Not just money!

56
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:51,733
If Edward failed as a son...

57
00:03:54,300 --> 00:04:00,600
maybe you failed
as a father, too!

58
00:04:04,367 --> 00:04:06,767
Dad, stop!

59
00:04:14,100 --> 00:04:15,600
You should thank
your older brother.

60
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:20,367
If it weren't for him,

61
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:22,833
I would've erased you
from my life a long time ago.

62
00:04:24,233 --> 00:04:25,233
Honestly...

63
00:04:27,967 --> 00:04:30,600
I don't even know
where you'll end up after this.

64
00:05:06,133 --> 00:05:07,433
Stop harassing us!

65
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:10,400
Just leave us alone!

66
00:05:13,367 --> 00:05:14,900
We're not running!

67
00:05:16,433 --> 00:05:17,600
Just...

68
00:05:18,900 --> 00:05:21,133
just leave us alone, please.

69
00:05:24,367 --> 00:05:26,167
<i> Thea?</i>

70
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:27,633
Thea, are you okay?

71
00:05:27,767 --> 00:05:29,000
Who were you talking to?

72
00:05:30,133 --> 00:05:33,133
No one. Just a business partner.

73
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:41,267
Edward's investors
have been harassing us.

74
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,933
They're blowing up
my phone, too.

75
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:47,200
The business collapsed.

76
00:05:49,733 --> 00:05:51,333
We're buried in debt.

77
00:05:55,433 --> 00:05:56,900
Since when?

78
00:05:57,033 --> 00:05:58,933
Why didn't you tell us?

79
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:05,700
I didn't want you to worry.

80
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:08,967
I didn't want to be a burden.

81
00:06:11,533 --> 00:06:14,833
You need to go back
to Cebu right away to fix this

82
00:06:14,967 --> 00:06:16,067
before it gets worse.

83
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:21,100
But, I don't think
it's safe there.

84
00:06:23,867 --> 00:06:26,233
One of the investors
told us...

85
00:06:29,933 --> 00:06:31,967
that if we go back to Cebu...

86
00:06:35,633 --> 00:06:37,867
my child and I could be
in danger.

87
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,200
What? If there's a threat,

88
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:42,300
we need to call the police.

89
00:06:42,467 --> 00:06:44,000
No, Marj.

90
00:06:44,133 --> 00:06:45,467
That won't work.

91
00:06:49,567 --> 00:06:54,367
The investor that Edward crossed
has powerful connections.

92
00:06:56,633 --> 00:06:57,867
That's why...

93
00:06:59,067 --> 00:07:01,267
I'd rather we stay here.

94
00:07:05,167 --> 00:07:06,900
We're safer here, Marj.

95
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:16,833
I'll feel more at ease
if my child and I stay here.

96
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:20,333
Nothing will happen to us here.

97
00:07:23,567 --> 00:07:27,133
Especially to Ashley.

98
00:07:56,167 --> 00:07:57,233
Death threat?

99
00:07:57,367 --> 00:07:59,600
Why are we only hearing
about this now?

100
00:07:59,733 --> 00:08:02,233
What if something happens
to Thea and Ashley?

101
00:08:02,367 --> 00:08:03,433
Greg, this is serious.

102
00:08:03,567 --> 00:08:05,300
Edward's life is in danger.

103
00:08:09,133 --> 00:08:14,333
Then we should get them a condo
or an apartment.

104
00:08:14,467 --> 00:08:18,267
They can't stay in this house.

105
00:08:19,533 --> 00:08:20,867
I agree with dad.

106
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,467
We have the resources.

107
00:08:23,167 --> 00:08:25,567
It's more practical to keep them
somewhere else.

108
00:08:27,433 --> 00:08:29,400
Love, why not here?

109
00:08:29,533 --> 00:08:31,000
We're all together.

110
00:08:31,133 --> 00:08:33,533
There are people here,
morning until night.

111
00:08:33,667 --> 00:08:34,900
There's CCTV.

112
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:37,600
They're safer here,
we have security gates.

113
00:08:37,733 --> 00:08:39,033
Exactly.

114
00:08:39,667 --> 00:08:44,100
If someone's threatening them,
why hide Ashley in an apartment

115
00:08:44,233 --> 00:08:46,433
when we can watch
over them here?

116
00:08:47,033 --> 00:08:49,633
Edward's family's lives
are on the line.

117
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:51,500
And then what?

118
00:08:51,633 --> 00:08:54,133
Turn our house
into a safe house?

119
00:08:55,033 --> 00:08:58,800
They've already overstayed
their welcome here.

120
00:08:58,933 --> 00:09:02,800
And let's not forget
why they're in trouble.

121
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:06,633
Edward caused this
in the first place.

122
00:09:07,700 --> 00:09:11,400
He wasted so much help
that we gave them.

123
00:09:12,667 --> 00:09:15,033
Dad, I know you're angry,

124
00:09:15,167 --> 00:09:16,967
and yes, Edward made mistakes.

125
00:09:17,100 --> 00:09:20,067
But please think
about Thea and Ashley.

126
00:09:20,767 --> 00:09:22,800
Their lives are at stake.

127
00:09:25,033 --> 00:09:27,933
Paolo, please, think about them.

128
00:09:28,100 --> 00:09:29,700
They need us,
they're scared.

129
00:09:29,833 --> 00:09:31,267
They need family.

130
00:09:33,833 --> 00:09:36,567
It's not that
I don't want them here.

131
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:39,467
It's just that...

132
00:09:43,900 --> 00:09:44,967
It's complicated.

133
00:09:50,567 --> 00:09:53,533
Maybe we can help them
in other ways.

134
00:09:53,667 --> 00:09:55,167
Oh, please!

135
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:58,667
I don't understand
why you're being so stubborn!

136
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:00,200
What if something happens
to Edward?

137
00:10:01,167 --> 00:10:05,333
Greg, what if something bad
happened to your granddaughter,

138
00:10:05,467 --> 00:10:08,033
and you realize
you could've saved them

139
00:10:08,167 --> 00:10:10,267
if you hadn't sent them away?

140
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:16,567
Could you live with that?

141
00:10:16,700 --> 00:10:20,367
Choosing your pride
and your anger over their lives?

142
00:10:27,167 --> 00:10:28,967
Dad...

143
00:10:29,100 --> 00:10:30,833
if the death threats are real,

144
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:35,400
I can't bear it
if something happens to them.

145
00:10:37,167 --> 00:10:38,433
To Thea...

146
00:10:38,567 --> 00:10:39,533
and to Edward.

147
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:41,767
Especially Ashley.

148
00:10:44,300 --> 00:10:46,567
Dad, Ashley is just a kid.

149
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:49,567
She doesn't deserve
to be caught in this.

150
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:52,200
She shouldn't pay
for Edward's mistakes.

151
00:10:53,333 --> 00:10:56,067
And if someone really
is after them...

152
00:10:57,033 --> 00:10:58,533
then they should stay here, Dad.

153
00:10:59,467 --> 00:11:00,733
Safe.

154
00:11:00,867 --> 00:11:01,633
Protected.

155
00:11:05,067 --> 00:11:06,533
Paolo.

156
00:11:06,667 --> 00:11:08,633
Dad, please.

157
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:11,800
I don't want anything bad
to happen to my niece.

158
00:11:22,533 --> 00:11:25,900
Yes! Finally!

159
00:11:26,033 --> 00:11:27,567
This is ours now.

160
00:11:27,700 --> 00:11:30,533
I can totally have
this redesigned.

161
00:11:30,667 --> 00:11:31,633
And I think it's time

162
00:11:31,767 --> 00:11:36,033
we move on from this whole
bachelor-cave vibe.

163
00:11:37,700 --> 00:11:40,900
And Ashley's getting
her own room here, too.

164
00:11:41,433 --> 00:11:43,233
Who knows? Before we know it,

165
00:11:43,367 --> 00:11:45,300
the whole mansion could be ours.

166
00:11:46,467 --> 00:11:47,700
You didn't have to make up
a story

167
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:49,900
just so we could stay here
for good.

168
00:11:50,733 --> 00:11:51,967
There are no death threats.

169
00:11:52,100 --> 00:11:55,867
You just made mom,
Paolo, Marj...

170
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:58,267
and even dad worry.

171
00:11:58,400 --> 00:12:00,600
Edward, seriously?

172
00:12:00,733 --> 00:12:03,200
How many times have we talked
about this?

173
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:06,833
If I didn't say that...

174
00:12:06,967 --> 00:12:09,100
do you think they'd let us stay?

175
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:13,400
But it's wrong.

176
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,533
We're lying to them.

177
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:18,867
Oh, and what's your alternative?

178
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:22,333
Go back to Cebu with creditors
breathing down our necks?

179
00:12:24,100 --> 00:12:28,100
Edward, you have no money left.

180
00:12:28,233 --> 00:12:31,367
No business,
no credibility.

181
00:12:32,367 --> 00:12:35,000
Pride doesn't put food
on the table.

182
00:12:35,133 --> 00:12:39,033
Pride doesn't pay off debt.

183
00:12:39,167 --> 00:12:43,900
And it sure doesn't give
our child security.

184
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:52,700
I got this.

185
00:12:54,367 --> 00:12:57,700
I'm the one finding a way for us
to bounce back, right?

186
00:12:58,667 --> 00:13:00,567
So instead of feeling guilty...

187
00:13:01,767 --> 00:13:03,600
you should be thanking me.

188
00:13:27,667 --> 00:13:30,433
What happened to Sir Edward
and Ma'am Thea

189
00:13:30,567 --> 00:13:33,900
was unbelievable, Miss, right?
From top-tier socialites

190
00:13:34,033 --> 00:13:36,500
to totally rock bottom,
and then, boom!

191
00:13:36,633 --> 00:13:40,000
They're back here with us.

192
00:13:40,133 --> 00:13:42,000
Well, at least the kids
are happy.

193
00:13:42,133 --> 00:13:44,633
Ashley and Jasmine
are close, right?

194
00:13:44,767 --> 00:13:45,800
Of course.

195
00:13:45,933 --> 00:13:49,667
But what about Ma'am Thea
living here now?

196
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:51,900
It's different
when you're just visiting.

197
00:13:52,033 --> 00:13:55,267
Now we see her every single day.

198
00:13:55,933 --> 00:13:59,333
Well, she and Ma'am Marj
get along, right?

199
00:14:01,100 --> 00:14:04,400
But didn't they have issues
before?

200
00:14:04,533 --> 00:14:06,667
Didn't they have some kind
of falling-out?

201
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:08,733
Probably just gossip.

202
00:14:16,367 --> 00:14:18,067
Wow, Jobert's really good
at that.

203
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:20,900
And you look so handsome
in your uniform.

204
00:14:21,033 --> 00:14:22,800
You look good.

205
00:14:22,933 --> 00:14:27,333
Sis, look, those edges
have to be perfect.

206
00:14:27,467 --> 00:14:30,900
If they're uneven,
I'll do it again.

207
00:14:32,700 --> 00:14:35,833
Marj, look at Jobert.

208
00:14:35,967 --> 00:14:38,300
Acting like a pro.

209
00:14:38,433 --> 00:14:41,767
Thanks, Marj, for helping him
get this job.

210
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:44,600
I'm really happy
he was hired here, Mom.

211
00:14:44,733 --> 00:14:48,033
And he looks happy
where he is now.

212
00:14:50,833 --> 00:14:51,900
Marj.

213
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:54,167
How about you, sweetheart?

214
00:14:54,967 --> 00:14:56,867
How are you?

215
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:59,267
How's life in the mansion?

216
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:01,867
How are things with Thea?

217
00:15:02,033 --> 00:15:04,100
Mom, we're fine.

218
00:15:04,233 --> 00:15:06,433
We've been fine for a long time.

219
00:15:06,567 --> 00:15:09,800
I just can't forget
what that woman did to you.

220
00:15:11,167 --> 00:15:15,133
Especially now that you're
living under the same roof.

221
00:15:15,267 --> 00:15:17,733
Marj, I'm worried.

222
00:15:17,867 --> 00:15:20,167
I don't want you
getting hurt again.

223
00:15:20,300 --> 00:15:24,133
Mom, that was over a decade ago.

224
00:15:24,267 --> 00:15:26,767
We both have our own families
now.

225
00:15:26,900 --> 00:15:29,233
And Thea was good to me
when I was pregnant

226
00:15:29,367 --> 00:15:30,933
with Jasmine.

227
00:15:31,067 --> 00:15:32,233
So we're okay.

228
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:37,700
Marj, I hope you don't trust
people too easily.

229
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:42,333
Not everyone who shows
they're good to you,

230
00:15:42,467 --> 00:15:44,667
isn't always the truth
in reality.

231
00:15:46,633 --> 00:15:51,233
Some people are nice
because they need something.

232
00:15:51,367 --> 00:15:56,067
Others stay quiet because
they're hiding something.

233
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:12,667
Paolo.

234
00:16:14,767 --> 00:16:16,400
Can I talk to you?

235
00:16:18,567 --> 00:16:19,733
Are you crazy?

236
00:16:20,633 --> 00:16:21,867
Why do you keep following me
around?

237
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,333
What if someone sees us?

238
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:26,300
Relax.

239
00:16:27,267 --> 00:16:30,067
I just wanted to say thank you.

240
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:31,700
No.

241
00:16:31,833 --> 00:16:33,033
Don't thank me.

242
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:37,333
I only agreed to let you stay
because of Ashley.

243
00:16:37,467 --> 00:16:39,467
I don't want the kid
getting hurt.

244
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:42,200
I know.

245
00:16:42,367 --> 00:16:43,933
And I appreciate it.

246
00:16:44,067 --> 00:16:45,567
No.

247
00:16:45,700 --> 00:16:47,233
You listen to me.

248
00:16:47,367 --> 00:16:51,467
If you cause one trouble
in this house,

249
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:55,600
no matter how small,
even just gossip,

250
00:16:55,733 --> 00:16:59,533
I'll make sure dad
kicks you out.

251
00:17:00,567 --> 00:17:02,667
No second chances.

252
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:04,567
No mercy.

253
00:17:06,267 --> 00:17:09,300
Paolo, I'm not the only one here

254
00:17:09,433 --> 00:17:12,200
with a history of causing
trouble, right?

255
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:14,567
Don't you dare.

256
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:16,700
This stays clean.

257
00:17:16,867 --> 00:17:18,333
You stay quiet.

258
00:17:18,467 --> 00:17:20,267
You stay out of the way.

259
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:22,333
No drama.

260
00:17:22,467 --> 00:17:24,400
Or we're done.

261
00:17:28,567 --> 00:17:32,833
We're done?

262
00:17:35,233 --> 00:17:36,933
Oh, so there's a "we"?

263
00:17:38,433 --> 00:17:40,300
That's not what I meant!

264
00:17:43,067 --> 00:17:45,233
<i> Paolo!</i>

265
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:48,333
<i> Paolo!</i>

266
00:17:48,733 --> 00:17:50,333
It's Marj!

267
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:02,400
<i> Paolo!</i>

268
00:18:04,467 --> 00:18:05,500
Love!

269
00:18:06,833 --> 00:18:08,600
- Love.
- What are you doing out here?

270
00:18:08,733 --> 00:18:09,767
It's late.

271
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:15,667
Nothing, just getting some air.

272
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:16,800
Trying to get sleepy.

273
00:18:18,767 --> 00:18:20,533
Okay, I just wanted
to remind you

274
00:18:20,667 --> 00:18:22,733
that Jasmine has a checkup
tomorrow.

275
00:18:23,667 --> 00:18:25,367
Of course, I didn't forget.

276
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:27,800
And Thea and Ashley
are coming, too.

277
00:18:27,933 --> 00:18:30,033
They have a dental appointment.

278
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:34,700
Sorry, Love, there's...

279
00:18:35,533 --> 00:18:38,533
I actually can't make it.
Something came up.

280
00:18:38,667 --> 00:18:39,833
Client meeting?

281
00:18:44,567 --> 00:18:45,633
Okay.

282
00:18:48,067 --> 00:18:49,967
Love...

283
00:18:50,100 --> 00:18:51,300
I'm sorry.

284
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:54,633
Promise, this is the last time.

285
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,500
Okay.

286
00:19:01,633 --> 00:19:03,733
Come on, let's go to bed.

287
00:19:03,867 --> 00:19:05,300
Okay.

288
00:19:05,433 --> 00:19:06,867
Come on?

289
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:28,067
Hi, Love!

290
00:19:34,067 --> 00:19:35,500
Hi.

291
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:43,867
You've been coming home late
a lot lately.

292
00:19:45,900 --> 00:19:47,100
There are lot of meetings.

293
00:19:50,533 --> 00:19:52,867
Are you avoiding someone
in this house?

294
00:19:55,900 --> 00:19:58,467
Are you avoiding me?

295
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:00,400
No, no.

296
00:20:00,533 --> 00:20:01,467
Let's not go there, Love.

297
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:03,667
Okay? We're still trying

298
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:05,367
to make time for each other,
right?

299
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:07,333
But that doesn't mean

300
00:20:07,467 --> 00:20:09,233
we have to stay stuck
inside this house.

301
00:20:10,233 --> 00:20:11,800
You know what, perfect timing.

302
00:20:11,933 --> 00:20:14,967
Mr. Zaragoza, is having
a farewell dinner this weekend,

303
00:20:15,100 --> 00:20:16,700
he's our outgoing board member.

304
00:20:17,467 --> 00:20:18,800
Mom and dad can't go.

305
00:20:18,933 --> 00:20:20,400
They've got a charity dinner.

306
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:24,700
Come with me, please?

307
00:20:27,767 --> 00:20:28,900
Love.

308
00:20:29,033 --> 00:20:30,733
Love, come on.

309
00:20:30,867 --> 00:20:32,267
You haven't joined me
in a get-together

310
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:33,367
for some quite time.

311
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:36,233
I'm always the only one
without a plus-one.

312
00:20:37,900 --> 00:20:41,400
Love, I can't keep up
with your colleagues anymore.

313
00:20:42,367 --> 00:20:46,333
While you're all talking
about stocks and investments,

314
00:20:46,467 --> 00:20:48,567
I'm thinking about our daughter.

315
00:20:48,700 --> 00:20:50,767
If she's taken her meds.

316
00:20:50,900 --> 00:20:52,600
When her next dose is.

317
00:20:52,733 --> 00:20:55,733
If mom and Jobert are okay.

318
00:20:57,300 --> 00:20:59,800
I don't vibe
with the trophy wives

319
00:20:59,933 --> 00:21:01,267
of your colleagues anymore.

320
00:21:02,533 --> 00:21:03,900
Okay, fine.

321
00:21:05,433 --> 00:21:07,200
Forget I asked.

322
00:21:07,333 --> 00:21:08,267
I'll just go change.

323
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,600
Excuse me.

324
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:25,100
Auntie.

325
00:21:25,233 --> 00:21:26,567
Look at this.

326
00:21:26,700 --> 00:21:27,900
It's mom and dad.

327
00:21:28,633 --> 00:21:30,500
Their aura back then
was insane, right?

328
00:21:31,367 --> 00:21:34,467
They looked like the CEO and
First Lady of Torrecampo Realty.

329
00:21:35,633 --> 00:21:39,500
Well, they really were a power
duo everywhere they went.

330
00:21:39,633 --> 00:21:40,800
Right? They looked so good
together.

331
00:21:40,933 --> 00:21:41,933
- They really did.
- Wow, it's beautiful.

332
00:21:42,100 --> 00:21:44,133
Mom was gorgeous.

333
00:21:44,267 --> 00:21:45,533
You guys look so happy.

334
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:48,467
Mom, look.

335
00:21:49,300 --> 00:21:51,033
You look so different.

336
00:21:52,300 --> 00:21:54,500
You're so young.

337
00:21:54,633 --> 00:21:55,967
And pretty.

338
00:21:56,100 --> 00:21:57,533
Used to.

339
00:21:59,367 --> 00:22:01,033
Right, Marj?

340
00:22:01,167 --> 00:22:04,100
That was before stress,
before mom life.

341
00:22:04,233 --> 00:22:06,467
Obviously, priorities change.

342
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:07,667
And eventually,

343
00:22:07,800 --> 00:22:10,200
I became Paolo's partner
at the office,

344
00:22:10,333 --> 00:22:14,333
while your mom was busy
being pregnant with you.

345
00:22:14,467 --> 00:22:17,300
- Auntie, I swear.
- Oh?

346
00:22:17,467 --> 00:22:20,233
How do you not age?

347
00:22:20,367 --> 00:22:21,800
Oh, come on!

348
00:22:21,933 --> 00:22:23,833
I mean, you're a mom too, right?

349
00:22:23,967 --> 00:22:27,600
As in. You look exactly the same
from 16 years ago.

350
00:22:27,733 --> 00:22:29,467
- Really?
- Really.

351
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:32,467
Oh, stop. It's just maintenance
and discipline.

352
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:34,167
And, of course,

353
00:22:34,300 --> 00:22:36,167
love from your Uncle Edward.

354
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:41,267
By the way, Marj,

355
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:42,833
mom talked to me.

356
00:22:42,967 --> 00:22:46,500
Edward and I are invited
to Mr. Zaragoza's farewell

357
00:22:46,633 --> 00:22:47,600
this weekend.

358
00:22:47,733 --> 00:22:50,133
Are you and Paolo going?

359
00:22:51,267 --> 00:22:52,833
I can't go with Paolo.

360
00:22:52,967 --> 00:22:55,567
I have too much to take care
of here at the house.

361
00:22:58,067 --> 00:22:59,067
I see.

362
00:23:00,433 --> 00:23:04,300
Actually, some of our former
coworkers messaged me.

363
00:23:04,433 --> 00:23:08,100
I don't know, they seemed
really excited to see me.

364
00:23:08,233 --> 00:23:11,233
They were saying
they can't believe

365
00:23:11,367 --> 00:23:14,633
I already have
a 15-year-old daughter.

366
00:23:14,767 --> 00:23:17,033
They said I'm like a vampire.

367
00:23:17,167 --> 00:23:18,333
Like I don't age.

368
00:23:18,467 --> 00:23:20,633
Like I haven't changed at all.

369
00:23:20,767 --> 00:23:22,600
Crazy, right?

370
00:23:22,767 --> 00:23:24,533
Gosh, I don't even know.

371
00:23:25,400 --> 00:23:27,067
Mom, look at you.

372
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:29,600
You were so beautiful,
seriously.

373
00:23:31,033 --> 00:23:32,433
That's right.

374
00:23:33,967 --> 00:23:34,967
Wow, Marj,

375
00:23:35,100 --> 00:23:38,433
you look like a completely
different person here.

376
00:23:39,767 --> 00:23:43,400
But you know,
with a little effort,

377
00:23:43,533 --> 00:23:45,367
you could totally bring
this back.

378
00:23:46,167 --> 00:23:48,700
Well, I think so.

379
00:23:48,833 --> 00:23:51,300
It's still possible.

380
00:23:52,300 --> 00:23:54,433
There's still hope.

381
00:23:54,567 --> 00:23:56,100
You were stunning.

382
00:23:58,033 --> 00:24:00,100
Such a waste, right?

383
00:24:00,233 --> 00:24:02,100
What happened?

384
00:24:06,167 --> 00:24:08,267
You looked really
different here, Marj.

385
00:24:11,133 --> 00:24:13,633
- Let me see again.
- Here, here.

386
00:24:17,633 --> 00:24:20,833
Yes, understated elegance
is rare these days.

387
00:24:20,967 --> 00:24:22,800
Everybody's trying too hard.

388
00:24:22,933 --> 00:24:25,267
- I know.
- Well, except for Thea.

389
00:24:25,533 --> 00:24:27,867
She's effortlessly beautiful.

390
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:28,967
I know.

391
00:24:29,133 --> 00:24:31,467
You know my son, Edward.

392
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:33,067
He has good taste.

393
00:24:33,200 --> 00:24:36,400
He knows a catch
when he sees it.

394
00:24:36,533 --> 00:24:38,733
Thank you, Mom.

395
00:24:38,867 --> 00:24:41,667
Honestly, you're my inspiration.

396
00:24:41,800 --> 00:24:45,000
I love your style
and how you carry yourself.

397
00:24:46,133 --> 00:24:49,433
Maybe that's where I got this
radiant, classy vibe.

398
00:24:49,567 --> 00:24:50,633
Oh, please!

399
00:24:50,767 --> 00:24:53,133
Isn't it obvious?

400
00:24:53,267 --> 00:24:55,867
And she tells the truth, too.

401
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:57,633
True.

402
00:25:02,300 --> 00:25:03,700
Look, Mom.

403
00:25:03,833 --> 00:25:06,867
Your favorite daughter-in-law
is here, too.

404
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:11,900
Hi, Marj! Come on, join us!

405
00:25:13,433 --> 00:25:15,133
Come here, you.

406
00:25:15,267 --> 00:25:17,100
Mom's friends are here.

407
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:20,933
Are you okay?

408
00:25:22,467 --> 00:25:24,600
Well, look at you, Marj.

409
00:25:24,733 --> 00:25:27,933
We heard you've been super busy
being a mom.

410
00:25:28,067 --> 00:25:31,333
That's why you barely make it
to our events anymore.

411
00:25:32,333 --> 00:25:34,767
I love your outfit.

412
00:25:34,900 --> 00:25:38,133
Very practical.

413
00:25:38,300 --> 00:25:40,733
It's rare these days to see
someone confident enough

414
00:25:40,867 --> 00:25:43,367
to be that comfortable.

415
00:25:46,367 --> 00:25:47,433
Oh, come on.

416
00:25:47,567 --> 00:25:49,167
Oh, you know Marj.

417
00:25:49,300 --> 00:25:53,400
She's juggling consultancy work
and taking care of Jasmine,

418
00:25:53,533 --> 00:25:56,267
who has special needs.

419
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:59,167
But honestly,
Marj is impressive.

420
00:25:59,300 --> 00:26:02,467
If she'd known you were coming,

421
00:26:02,600 --> 00:26:06,100
I'm sure she would've dressed up
a little more.

422
00:26:06,233 --> 00:26:09,433
Oh, I'm sure she would have.
Knowing Marj.

423
00:26:11,233 --> 00:26:12,867
Come on, Marj.

424
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:14,767
You knew I had guests,

425
00:26:14,900 --> 00:26:18,700
and you're walking around
looking like that?

426
00:26:26,433 --> 00:26:27,400
Thea's taking forever.

427
00:26:27,533 --> 00:26:28,667
You know how she is.

428
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:30,767
At events like this, she really
goes all out getting ready.

429
00:26:30,900 --> 00:26:33,133
Honestly, Marj,
you made the right call

430
00:26:33,267 --> 00:26:35,767
not coming
to Mr. Zaragoza's dinner.

431
00:26:35,900 --> 00:26:37,000
You'd just stress yourself out.

432
00:26:37,133 --> 00:26:38,500
Hon, you look amazing.

433
00:26:38,633 --> 00:26:40,033
Hi, Paolo.

434
00:26:40,167 --> 00:26:42,567
I hope it's not too late
to change my mind.

435
00:26:43,367 --> 00:26:44,833
I'm going with you.

436
00:26:44,967 --> 00:26:49,933
Thea, we're planning to have
a quick getaway in Cebu!

437
00:26:50,067 --> 00:26:51,400
You want to come?

438
00:26:51,533 --> 00:26:52,467
I'm game.

439
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:53,733
Why did you say yes?

440
00:26:53,867 --> 00:26:55,400
What about the death threats?

441
00:26:55,533 --> 00:26:58,233
Come on, I'm not actually going,
okay?

442
00:26:58,367 --> 00:27:00,000
And, of course,
I haven't forgotten about

443
00:27:00,133 --> 00:27:03,000
the so-called death threats
from those loan sharks in Cebu.

444
00:27:03,133 --> 00:27:04,300
Loan sharks?

445
00:27:04,433 --> 00:27:05,800
What's the truth?

446
00:27:05,933 --> 00:27:08,500
Are there really death threats,
or did you just make them up?
